# MINI_SOC_PROJECT_ROADMAP_v1.0

# 1. Project Objective

Build and verify a complete Mini SoC using SystemVerilog.

Primary Goal:

```
Learn SoC Verification Concepts
```

Secondary Goal:

```
Learn RTL Design Concepts
```

The project shall progress from:

```
Registers
    ↓
APB
    ↓
Verification
    ↓
Multiple IPs
    ↓
Integration
    ↓
AXI-Lite
    ↓
SoC Verification
    ↓
UVM Migration
```

---

# 2. Learning Roadmap

The roadmap is divided into 5 major stages.

Stage-1

```
Foundation
```

Stage-2

```
Block-Level Verification
```

Stage-3

```
Integration Verification
```

Stage-4

```
SoC Verification
```

Stage-5

```
UVM Migration
```

---

# 3. Stage-1 Foundation

## Objective

Learn register verification fundamentals.

---

# Phase-1

APB Interface

Deliverables:

```
apb_if.sv
```

Learn:

```
APB protocol
```

Concepts:

```
Setup Phase
Access Phase
Read
Write
```

Success Criteria:

```
APB timing fully understood
```

---

# Phase-2

GPIO RTL

Deliverables:

```
gpio_apb.sv
```

Registers:

```
GPIO_CTRL
GPIO_DIR
GPIO_DATA_OUT
GPIO_DATA_IN
GPIO_STATUS
```

Learn:

```
Register implementation
```

Concepts:

```
RW
RO
RW1C
```

Success Criteria:

```
GPIO simulation works
```

---

# Phase-3

APB Master BFM

Deliverables:

```
apb_master_bfm.sv
```

Tasks:

```
apb_write()
apb_read()
```

Learn:

```
Bus Functional Modeling
```

Success Criteria:

```
Register accesses automated
```

---

# Phase-4

GPIO Verification

Tests:

```
GPIO_001
GPIO_002
GPIO_003
GPIO_004
```

Learn:

```
Register verification
```

Concepts:

```
Reset testing
Read/write testing
RO testing
```

Success Criteria:

```
All GPIO tests pass
```

